      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Conservation is a welcome sentiment from this administration (front page, Sept. 27).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Conservation is a welcome sentiment from this administration (front page, Sept. 27).</p>
        <p>Yes, we can all take fewer car trips, turn off lights and computers and switch to more efficient appliances. And we should.</p>
        <p>But as individuals, we won't be able to conserve our way out of our energy mess.</p>
        <p>It's up to the president and Congress to adopt federal policies that encourage economy-wide conservation, fuel efficiency and clean, renewable energy sources.</p>
        <p>Karen Perry Stillerman  Washington, Sept. 27, 2005</p>
      </block>
